fine in normalmap shader named \"PHYSICALLY_BASED_SHADING\" just enables the Fresnel term ... and thus it should be renamed as such to be more precise:\n\n`renderer.physicallyBasedShading` flag should be removed and made the default. The literature supports that approach.\n\nIt is adding a normalization constant to get the specular highlight correct -- in addition to the Fresnel term.\n\nAlso, perhaps the \"Angle bug\" is no longer an issue, and the hack can be removed. The hack occurs elsewhere, BTW.\n","created_at":"2014-01-02T19:04:00.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4256#issuecomment-31475535","id":31475535,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4256","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxNDc1NTM1","updated_at":"2014-01-02T19:04:00.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/31475535","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"> Probably should settle on a single standard here.\n\nYes, the `normalmap` shader is somewhat of an oddball. I'd make it consistent with how `phong` is done.\n\n> I'd suggest as going as far as creating a 'surface_colors' section in the ShaderLib.js for \"diffuseColor\", \"ambientColor\", \"emissiveColor\" and \"specularColor\" (I'd recommend including \"Color\" in the name to be clear what it is) as it is pretty common and making it standardized just simplifies things.\n\nActually, they are reflectances (except for `emissive`). `ambient` is the _ambient reflectance of the material_. Personally, I think the short forms for the names are fine.\n\nAs a convenience to the user, we have used the word \"color\" for \"diffuse\".\n","created_at":"2014-01-02T19:23:08.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4256#issuecomment-31477021","id":31477021,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4256","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxNDc3MDIx","updated_at":"2014-01-02T19:23:08.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/31477021","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com